        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 5:05AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 505 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles south of Clarendon, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Clarendon, Hedley, Lelia Lake, and Greenbelt Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
